<paragraph id="8B4936A51610FFAEFF2BFAE7FECCFF24" blockId="4.[151,939,1311,1372]" box="[151,287,1346,1372]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
(
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201610FFAEFF23FAE7FEC6FF24" box="[159,277,1346,1372]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 9–16" captionStart-1="FIGURES 17–19" captionStartId-0="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionStartId-1="6.[151,269,1170,1194]" captionTargetBox-0="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetBox-1="[174,1416,189,1133]" captionTargetId-0="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetId-1="figure-247@6.[157,1442,181,1151]" captionTargetPageId-0="5" captionTargetPageId-1="6" captionText-0="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." captionText-1="FIGURES 17–19. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov., female paratype: (17) sternite VII, ventral view; (18) pygofer, lateral view; (19) second valvula, lateral view (the arrow indicates the truncate basal limit)." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321362" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/5321362/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Figs 9–19</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B4936A51610FFAEFF2BFA2AFBB8FFD2" blockId="4.[151,1436,1423,2030]" box="[151,1131,1423,1450]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B982EAB71610FFAEFF2BFA2AFF29FFD1" bold="true" box="[151,250,1423,1449]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Length:</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus id="544D88071610FFAEFEF9FA35FE7CFFD2" box="[325,431,1424,1450]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">holotype</typeStatus>
, 5.7 mm; male 
<typeStatus id="544D88071610FFAEFDDFFA35FD18FFD2" box="[611,715,1424,1450]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">paratype</typeStatus>
, 5.4 mm; female 
<typeStatus id="544D88071610FFAEFC2BFA35FC2CFFD2" box="[919,1023,1424,1450]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">paratype</typeStatus>
, 6.4 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B4936A51610FFAEFF79FA13FE31FC13" blockId="4.[151,1436,1423,2030]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis id="B982EAB71610FFAEFF79FA13FE57FFA8" bold="true" box="[197,388,1462,1488]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
Male 
<typeStatus id="544D88071610FFAEFEB2FA13FEACFFA8" box="[270,383,1462,1488]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Head (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201610FFAEFE63FA13FD8EFFA8" box="[479,605,1462,1488]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Figs 9, 10</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, well produced anteriorly, anterior margin rounded; crown with median length 2/3 interocular width and 2/5 transocular width; epicranial suture weakly visible, temporal and frontogenal sutures distinct. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201610FFAEFCA5F9A1FC45FC66" box="[793,918,1540,1566]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Figs 9, 10</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, with width approximately equal to transocular width. Forewings (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201610FFAEFDDCF98FFD76FC3C" box="[608,677,1578,1604]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) with membrane distinct on apical portion, including apical cells and apex of anteapical cells.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B4936A51610FFAEFF79F9DDFEF6FCA7" blockId="4.[151,1436,1423,2030]" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
Dorsum (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201610FFAEFE89F9DDFE62FCEA" box="[309,433,1656,1682]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Figs 9, 10</figureCitation>
) dark brown with numerous small yellow maculae. Crown with yellow line behind eyes. Face dark brown with yellow maculae on frons, genae, and antennal ledges. Venter dark brown. Legs pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B4936A51610FFAFFF79F949FA9BFA87" blockId="4.[151,1436,1423,2030]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,152,255]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">
Pygofer (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201610FFAEFE8DF949FE56FD7E" box="[305,389,1772,1798]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with macrosetae on apical portion and extending anteriorly along ventral margin; apical portion with apicoventral inner process bearing numerous setae. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201610FFAEFAA4F8B7FABCFD54" box="[1304,1391,1810,1836]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, narrowing gradually toward apex, with macrosetae near outer margin of ventral surface, and with some setae on dorsal surface. Styles (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201610FFAEFD1DF8C5FD2FFD02" box="[673,764,1888,1914]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, extending posteriorly beyond apex of connective; with distinct median lobe on outer margin; portion beyond lobe curved; apex truncate. Connective (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201610FFAEFF1CF808FF2BFDBF" box="[160,248,1965,1991]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, Y-shaped. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201610FFAEFD76F808FCF1FDBF" box="[714,802,1965,1991]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="47">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with shaft slightly curved ventrally; apical portion expanded with distinct dorsal lobe; median portion with laterodorsal expansion bearing small setae. Paraphyses (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201611FFAFFECEFF3DFE2BFACA" box="[370,504,152,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–16" captionStartId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" captionTargetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" captionTargetId="figure-131@5.[151,1436,278,1852]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–16. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov.: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Figs 15, 16</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, X-shaped; pair of rami directed anteriorly narrow, pair directed posteriorly broadened toward apex; stalk approximately as long as anterior rami. Anal tube (segment X), in ventral view, with pair of apical areas on ventral margin with setae similar to those of pygofer process.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF89662D1611FFAFFF2BF8F1FC4FFDAF" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321358" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5321358" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321358/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" startId="5.[151,271,1876,1900]" targetBox="[164,1416,309,1828]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="8B4936A51611FFAFFF2BF8F1FC4FFDAF" blockId="5.[151,1436,1876,2007]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis id="B982EAB71611FFAFFF2BF8F1FE80FD14" bold="true" box="[151,339,1876,1900]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">FIGURES 9–16.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4CF64D261611FFAFFEE7F8F1FDB6FD13" box="[347,613,1876,1899]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Exogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavomaculata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B982EAB71611FFAFFEE7F8F1FDB6FD13" box="[347,613,1876,1899]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Exogonia flavomaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B982EAB71611FFAFFDD1F8F3FD68FD13" bold="true" box="[621,699,1878,1899]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2B157CC1611FFAFFDD1F8F3FD68FD13" box="[621,699,1878,1899]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
: (9) body of male holotype, lateral view; (10) head, pronotum, and mesonotum of male paratype, dorsal view; (11-16) male holotype: (11) pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view; (12) subgenital plate, ventral view; (13) connective and style, dorsal view; (14) aedeagus and basal portion of gonoduct, lateral view; (15) paraphyses, lateral view; (16) paraphyses, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DF89662D1612FFACFF2BFB37FBC9FEB5" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321362" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5321362" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321362/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" startId="6.[151,269,1170,1194]" targetBox="[174,1416,189,1133]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph id="8B4936A51612FFACFF2BFB37FBC9FEB5" blockId="6.[151,1436,1170,1229]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B982EAB71612FFACFF2BFB37FE8FFED2" bold="true" box="[151,348,1170,1194]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">FIGURES 17–19.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4CF64D261612FFACFEDFFB36FDBBFED2" box="[355,616,1171,1194]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Exogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavomaculata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B982EAB71612FFACFEDFFB36FDBBFED2" box="[355,616,1171,1194]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">Exogonia flavomaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B982EAB71612FFACFDD1FB31FD6AFED1" bold="true" box="[621,697,1172,1193]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2B157CC1612FFACFDD1FB31FD6AFED1" box="[621,697,1172,1193]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, female paratype: (17) sternite VII, ventral view; (18) pygofer, lateral view; (19) second valvula, lateral view (the arrow indicates the truncate basal limit).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B4936A51612FFACFF79FAA4FB66FC52" blockId="6.[151,1436,1281,1887]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B982EAB71612FFACFF79FAA4FD36FF63" bold="true" box="[197,741,1281,1307]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">
Female genitalia (based on 
<specimenCount id="9DF0FD2C1612FFACFD95FAA4FD04FF63" box="[553,727,1281,1307]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" type="generic" typeStatus="paratype">one paratype</specimenCount>
).
</emphasis>
Sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201612FFACFC2DFAA4FC39FF63" box="[913,1002,1281,1307]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–19" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1170,1194]" captionTargetBox="[174,1416,189,1133]" captionTargetId="figure-247@6.[157,1442,181,1151]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–19. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov., female paratype: (17) sternite VII, ventral view; (18) pygofer, lateral view; (19) second valvula, lateral view (the arrow indicates the truncate basal limit)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321362" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321362/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
) broader than long; lateral margins approximately rectilinear; posterior margin with distinct concavity medially; surface with small setae, mostly on posterior portion, and very few longitudinal striae on median portion. Pygofer (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201612FFACFBC5FAEAFB01FF11" box="[1145,1234,1359,1385]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–19" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1170,1194]" captionTargetBox="[174,1416,189,1133]" captionTargetId="figure-247@6.[157,1442,181,1151]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–19. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov., female paratype: (17) sternite VII, ventral view; (18) pygofer, lateral view; (19) second valvula, lateral view (the arrow indicates the truncate basal limit)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321362" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321362/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with posterior margin narrowly rounded; macrosetae on posterior portion, extending anteriorly along ventral margin. Second valvulae (
<figureCitation id="13CD2A201612FFACFE62FA39FDE8FFCE" box="[478,571,1436,1462]" captionStart="FIGURES 17–19" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1170,1194]" captionTargetBox="[174,1416,189,1133]" captionTargetId="figure-247@6.[157,1442,181,1151]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 17–19. Exogonia flavomaculata sp. nov., female paratype: (17) sternite VII, ventral view; (18) pygofer, lateral view; (19) second valvula, lateral view (the arrow indicates the truncate basal limit)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5321362" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5321362/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, moderately expanded beyond basal curvature; shaft narrowing slightly toward subacute apex; preapical prominence small but distinct; teeth extending from expanded basal portion to apical portion, basal teeth large and rectangular, followed by gradually smaller ones; teeth and dorsal and ventral margins of anteapical portion of shaft bearing denticles.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B4936A51612FFACFF79F993FD22FCE6" blockId="6.[151,1436,1281,1887]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B982EAB71612FFACFF79F993FBDBFC28" bold="true" box="[197,1032,1590,1616]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">
Intraspecific variation (based on all male and female 
<typeStatus id="544D88071612FFACFCC2F993FBD3FC28" box="[894,1024,1590,1616]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">paratypes</typeStatus>
)
</emphasis>
. Crown sometimes with anterior margin narrowly rounded and epicranial, temporal, and frontogenal sutures very distinct. Female 
<typeStatus id="544D88071612FFACFA89F9F8FA4FFC0F" box="[1333,1436,1629,1655]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">paratype</typeStatus>
with median length of crown 1/2 transocular width.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3EC652E1612FFACFF79F90FFCC9FD27" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B4936A51612FFACFF79F90FFEACFC93" blockId="6.[151,1436,1281,1887]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis id="B982EAB71612FFACFF79F90FFE85FCBC" bold="true" box="[197,342,1706,1732]" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet, 
<taxonomicName id="4CF64D261612FFACFDDFF90EFCC2FCBC" box="[611,785,1707,1732]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Exogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavomaculata">
<emphasis id="B982EAB71612FFACFDDFF90EFCC2FCBC" box="[611,785,1707,1732]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="49">flavomaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is of Latin derivation and refers to the small yellow maculae of dorsum.
</paragraph>
